Jose Toledo Luna

Bio

I am currently a Statistics Ph.D.student at UCLA. Prior to joining UCLA, I obtained my BA and MS degrees in Statistics from California State University, Fullerton.

Teaching Experience

California State University, Fullerton

  • Math 115: College Algebra (Fall 2019)
  • Math 120: Elementary Statistics (Spring 2020, Fall 2020)
  • Math 338: Statistics Applied to Natural Sciences (Spring 2021)

Publications

  • Luna, J., Jaynes, J., Xu, H., Wong, W. K. (2022). Orthogonal Array Composite Designs for Drug Combination Experiments with Applications to Tuberculosis. Statistics in Medicine
